      <p>Most homeowners don't think about their gutters until something goes wrong. But blocked gutters are one of the most common — and most avoidable — causes of serious water damage in Irish homes. Leaves, moss, debris, and dirt pile up over time. When rainwater has nowhere to go, it spills over, soaks into walls, and can rot your fascias and soffits. Left long enough, you're looking at damp problems, structural repairs, and a hefty bill.</p>
